{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 06:48:43.972169", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope\n- Detect anomalies\n- Localize faulty devices (if any)\n- Identify root cause(s)\n\nSummary\n- Overall network health appears normal. End-to-end reachability, DNS resolution, and HTTP access to the server farm (including the load balancer) are working from both access hosts.\n- Backend web server subnet is intentionally unreachable from user subnets, consistent with the stated design.\n\nAccess Hosts (IP/DHCP/Default Route)\n- host_1_1_1_1: 10.1.1.10/24 via DHCP, default gw 10.1.1.1\n  - Lease reported as dynamic with short valid_lft (~40s), which indicates DHCP is active; timing likely a lab setting.\n- host_2_1_1_1: 10.2.1.20/24 via DHCP, default gw 10.2.1.1\n  - Similarly dynamic lease, valid_lft ~33s.\n\nInter-host Connectivity\n- host_1_1_1_1 -> host_2_1_1_1: ICMP reachable (0% loss, ~2.7–6.6 ms RTT)\n\nDNS\n- resolv.conf on both hosts: nameserver 10.200.0.2 (dns_server)\n- host_1_1_1_1 -> dns_server (10.200.0.2): ICMP reachable (0% loss)\n- host_2_1_1_1 -> dns_server: ICMP reachable (0% loss)\n- Name lookups during HTTP tests are fast and consistent, indicating functional DNS.\n\nHTTP/Web Services\n- Direct web servers (web0.local etc.):\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> web0.local: HTTP OK; total times ~1.0–1.22 s\n  - host_2_1_1_1 -> web0.local: HTTP OK; total times ~1.00–1.41 s\n  - ICMP to web_server_0 (10.200.0.3) succeeds from both hosts (0% loss)\n- Load balancer (web99.local at 10.200.0.7):\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> web99.local: HTTP OK; total times ~1.02–1.09 s\n  - host_2_1_1_1 -> web99.local: HTTP OK; total times ~1.00–1.13 s\n  - ICMP to 10.200.0.7 succeeds from both hosts (0% loss)\n- Backend web server access:\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> backend_web_0 (20.200.0.2): Destination Net Unreachable from 10.1.1.1\n  - host_2_1_1_1 -> backend_web_0 (20.200.0.2): Destination Net Unreachable from 10.2.1.1\n  - This matches design: backend servers are not directly accessible from user hosts.\n\nRouting/OSPF (FRR samples)\n- router_dist_1_1:\n  - C 10.1.1.0/24 connected (br0); OSPF routes present for 10.2.x/24 and 10.200.0.0/24 via uplink (172.16.0.6).\n- router_dist_2_1:\n  - C 10.2.1.0/24 connected (br0); OSPF routes present for 10.1.x/24 and 10.200.0.0/24 via uplink (172.16.0.14).\n- router_core_1:\n  - OSPF has routes to access subnets and to 10.200.0.0/24 via server side (172.16.0.3). Some ECMP on inter-core links observed; normal in a hierarchical design.\n- server_access_router:\n  - C 10.200.0.0/24 connected (br0), OSPF routes to all access subnets via core. No route for 20.200.0.0/24 in any distribution router, consistent with backend isolation.\n\nDetected Anomalies\n- None impacting service delivery identified.\n- Observed “Destination Net Unreachable” to 20.200.0.2 from user VLANs is expected by design (backend isolation; no route advertised to user areas).\n\nLocalization of Faulty Devices\n- No faulty devices localized. All tested components (hosts, distribution routers, core, server access router, DNS, load balancer, and web servers) exhibit expected behavior.\n\nRoot Cause Analysis (for notable observations)\n- Inaccessibility of backend_web_0 from user hosts: Root cause is intentional network segmentation/policy—backend subnet (20.200.0.0/24) is not advertised into user subnets via OSPF, and gateways return net-unreachable. This matches the stated design goal that backend web servers are not directly accessible.\n\nAdditional Notes\n- DHCP lease timers on hosts are very short (tens of seconds), likely a lab configuration; not a functional issue.\n- Latency varies between ~2–13 ms in a few ICMP samples; within typical lab virtualization variance; no loss observed.\n\nOverall Assessment\n- Network is healthy. OSPF routing is consistent, DNS is reachable and resolving, direct web servers and the HTTP load balancer are accessible from both access hosts, and backend server isolation is enforced as designed. No abnormal behavior requiring remediation detected.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11950, "output_tokens": 3803, "total_tokens": 15753, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7552}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2624}}}
